<subsection xml:id="Interior-angles-of-a-polygon">
        <title>Interior angles of a polygon</title>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                Interior angles of a polygon are the angles within a polygon made by two sides.
            </p>
            <p>
                We can calculate the sum of the interior angles of a polygon by subtracting 2 from the number of sides and then multiplying by <m>180^\circ</m>.
            </p>
        </introduction>

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Triangle">
        <title>Triangle</title>

        <activity>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <term>Sum of the interior angles in a triangle</term>
                </p>
                <p>
                    We know that the angles in any triangle add up to <m>180^\circ.</m>
                </p>

                    <image width="50%">
                        <latex-image>
                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                            \draw [blue,thick](0,0)coordinate(A)--(0,6)coordinate (B)--(6,0)coordinate(C)--(0,0)coordinate(A);
                            \draw node at(-0.2,0){A};
                            \draw node at (0,6.2){B};
                            \draw node at (6.2,0){C};
                            \draw node at (2,3){$180^\circ$};
                            
                            \end{tikzpicture}
                        </latex-image> 
                    </image>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the sum of interior angles for a triangle is <m>180^\circ.</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            
        </activity>

    </subsubsection>

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Rectangle">
        <title>Rectangle</title>
                <activity>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <term>Sum of the interior angles in a rectangle</term>
                        </p>

                        

                        <p>
                            To find the sum of interior angles of the rectangle below;
                        </p>

                            <image width="50%">
                                <latex-image>
                                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                                    \draw[green,thick](0,0) coordinate (A)-- (6,0) coordinate (B)-- (6,4) coordinate (C)--(0,4)coordinate(D)--(0,0)coordinate(A); 
                                    \end{tikzpicture}
                                </latex-image>
                            </image>

                        <p>
                            We can split the rectangle into two triangles by drawing a line from one corner to an opposite one.      
                        </p>
                        
                        <sidebyside widths="50% 50%">
                            <image>
                                <shortdescription>Rectangle</shortdescription>
                                <latex-image>
                                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                                        \draw[thick,green](0,0)--(6,0)--(6,3)--(0,3)--(0,0);
                                    \end{tikzpicture}
                                </latex-image>
                                
                            </image>

                            <image>
                                <shortdescription>Rectangle2</shortdescription>
                                <latex-image>
                                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                                        \draw[thick,green](0,0)--(6,0)--(6,3)--(0,3)--(0,0);
                                        \draw[thick,green](0,3)--(6,0);
                                        \draw node at (0.5,1.5){$180^\circ$};
                                        \draw node at (4.5,1.5){$180^\circ$};
                                    \end{tikzpicture}
                                </latex-image>
                                
                            </image>

                        </sidebyside>

                        <p>
                                The sum of interior angles one triangle is <m>180^\circ.</m> Therefore, the sum of the interior angles of the  two triangles in the rectangle is <m>180^\circ \times 2   = 360^\circ</m>      
                        </p>
                                    
                        <p>
                            <term> Properties of a rectangle.  </term>
                        </p>
                                    
                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        A rectangle has four sides. 
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                            
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        It has four interior angles.
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                        
                            
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        Each interior angle is <m>90^\circ</m> (right angle).
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                        
                        
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        The sum of interior angles in a rectangle is <m>360^\circ</m>
                                    </p>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <p>
                                        The sum of interior angles is equal to four right angles.
                                    </p>
                                </li>

                            </ul>

                        </p>
                                    
                    </statement>
                </activity>

    </subsubsection>

