    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-Summary">
    <title>Summary</title>
    <p>
        <term>In order to find the sum of interior angles of any polygon:</term>
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Identify the number of sides of the polygon. Check if the polygon is regular or irregular.
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    Work out how many triangles could be created within the polygon by drawing lines from a single vertex to all the other vertices
                </p>
            </li>

            <li>
                <p>
                    Multiply the number of triangles in the polygon by <m>180^\circ</m> to find the sum of the interior angles.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p> 
    </subsubsection>

</subsection>